# LLM Gateway Standards

**Timeouts**: Set per LLM call, tool call, and total request budget. Propagate cancellation on client disconnect.

**Retries**: Idempotent reads only; exponential backoff with jitter; cap attempts. Never blind-retry write tools.

**Circuit breaker**: Open on sustained LLM/provider failures; fail fast with user-friendly message and audit event.

**Errors**: Structured internal errors with `trace_id`; map to generic customer responses. No provider stack traces outward.

**Rate limits**: Enforce per user/session/org before LLM invocation. Return 429 with Retry-After where applicable.

**Logging**: Log latency, model id, token counts (aggregated) — not full prompts in production info logs.
